title.rendered: Emirates vs Dubai, Eliminator, International T20 League 2023: Fantasy Team, Probable Playing XIs, Pitch Report & Fantasy Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable Playing XIs for Emirates & Dubai

Emirates: Andre Fletcher, Muhammad Waseem, Nicholas Pooran (wk), Lorcan Tucker, Kieron Pollard (c), Dwayne Bravo, Dan Mousley, Trent Boult, Imran Tahir, Fazalhaq Farooqi, Zahoor Khan

Dubai: George Munsey, Robin Uthappa (wk), Sikandar Raza, Dasun Shanaka, Rovman Powell, Yusuf Pathan (c), Adam Zampa, Fred Klaassen, Jake Ball, Hazrat Luqman, Akif Raja

Pitch Report for Emirates vs Dubai

Venue: Sharjah Cricket Stadium, Sharjah

(Based on the last three games)

1st innings average score: 165

2nd innings average score: 114

Wickets per innings: 7

Type: Difficult to chase

Wins

Batting 1st: 67%

Batting 2nd: 33%

Also Read:

India vs Pakistan, Women’s T20 World Cup 2023: Fantasy Tips

Australia vs New Zealand, Women’s T20 World Cup 2023: Fantasy Tips

Joburg vs Eastern Cape, Semi-final, South Africa T20 League 2023: Fantasy Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day

The top fantasy players in this contest are Rovman Powell (320 runs, 5 wickets, 5 catches) and Kieron Pollard (337 runs, 2 wickets, 5 catches). The battle for captaincy and vice-captaincy will be between these two Caribbean marauders.

The conditions in the UAE seem to have favoured Adam Zampa. Ever since his participation in the league, his bowling figures read 3 for 16, 3 for 16, 1 for 20, and 2 for 24.

In the last 10 T20s, Sikandar Raza has blasted 239 runs at 48 and taken 4 wickets.

Muhammad Waseem has been scoring the majority of the runs at the top. He has scored two fifties and two thirties in the last four outings.

The last time these teams squared off, Robin Uthappa (58* off 36, a catch, a run out) and Dasun Shanaka (56* off 36) were the captain and vice-captain of the Ultimate Team.

In the last three games at the venue, pacers accounted for 27 of 40 wickets.
